spite%20their%20past%20successful%20projects.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Salman%20Khan's%20planned%20action%20film%20with%20director%20Atlee%20is%20delayed%20due%20to%20Rajinikanth's%20busy%20schedule%2C%20and%20budget%20issues%20regarding%20casting%20decisions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fkabir-khan-clarifies-he-is-not-working-on-babbar-sher-with-salman-khan-i-think-when-i-went-to-meet-him-%2Farticleshow%2F118760677.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Why%20so%20much%20indifference%20towards%20Maa%20Ganga%3F'%20Kharge%20targets%20PM%20Modi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741262766000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-118761880%2Cimgsize-1390835.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fwhy-so-much-indifference-towards-maa-ganga-congress-president-kharge-targets-pm-modi-over-pending-namami-gange-projects%2Farticleshow%2F118761609.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Congress%20president%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20criticized%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20over%20pending%20projects%20under%20the%20Namami%20Gange%20scheme%2C%20accusing%20the%20government%20of%20underutilizing%20funds%20and%20failing%20to%20meet%20deadlines.%20Kharge%20cited%20a%20government%20reply%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%20to%20highlight%20significant%20percentages%20of%20incomplete%20work%20under%20the%20scheme.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fwhy-so-much-indifference-towards-maa-ganga-congress-president-kharge-targets-pm-modi-over-pending-namami-gange-projects%2Farticleshow%2F118761609.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22H-1B%20Visa%3A%20Why%20US%20Wants%20Employers%20To%20Hire%20Americans%20Over%20Migrant%20Workers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20administration's%20efforts%20to%20challenge%20what%20it%20deems%20as%20illegal%20hiring%20preferences%20for%20foreign%20workers%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20program%2C%20has%20caused%20apprehension%20among%20the%20immigrant%20community.%20At%20the%20heart%20of%20this%20controversy%20lies%20the%20Equal%20Employment%20Opportunity%20Commission's%20(EEOC)%20investigation%20into%20the%20matter%2C%20aimed%20at%20safeguarding%20jobs%20for%20US%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20stern%20warning%20issued%20on%20February%2019%2C%202025%2C%20businesses%20were%20cautioned%20against%20prioritising%20foreign%20workers%20over%20American%20candidates%2C%20with%20EEOC's%20acting%20chair%2C%20Andrea%20Lucas%2C%20highlighting%20the%20pervasive%20nature%20of%20national%20origin%20discrimination%20in%20hiring%20across%20multiple%20industries%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Business%20Standard%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noindex%2Cnofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fh-1b-visa-conundrum-no-anti-american-bias-migrant-preference-warns-us-125030400371_1.html%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnlawful%20bias%20against%20American%20workers%2C%20in%20violation%20of%20Title%20VII%2C%20is%20a%20large-scale%20problem%20in%20multiple%20industries%20nationwide%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lucas.%20%26quot%3BMany%20employers%20have%20policies%20and%20practices%20preferring%20illegal%20aliens%2C%20migrant%20workers%2C%20and%20visa%20holders%20or%20other%20legal%20immigrants%20over%20American%20workers-in%20direct%20violation%20of%20federal%20employment%20law.%20Cracking%20down%20on%20this%20type%20of%20unlawful%20discrimination%20will%20shift%20employer%20incentives%2C%20decreasing%20demand%20for%20illegal%20alien%20workers%20and%20decreasing%20abuse%20of%20the%20United%20States'%20legal%20immigration%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELucas%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20EEOC%20is%20putting%20employers%20and%20other%20covered%20entities%20on%20notice%3A%20if%20you%20are%20part%20of%20the%20pipeline%20contributing%20to%20our%20immigration%20crisis%20or%20abusing%20our%20legal%20immigration%20system%20via%20illegal%20preferences%20against%20American%20workers%2C%20you%20must%20stop.%20The%20law%20applies%20to%20you%2C%20and%20you%20are%20not%20above%20the%20law.%20The%20EEOC%20is%20here%20to%20protect%20all%20workers%20from%20unlawful%20national%20origin%20discrimination%2C%20including%20American%20workers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20H-1B%20visa%20program%2C%20which%20enables%20US%20companies%20to%20hire%20foreign%20professionals%20in%20fields%20requiring%20a%20degree%2C%20such%20as%20technology%2C%20engineering%20and%20medical%20sciences%2C%20has%20come%20under%20scrutiny.%20Critics%20argue%20that%20this%20program%20displaces%20American%20workers%2C%20with%20some%20employers%20allegedly%20favouring%20foreign%20workers%20due%20to%20lower%20labour%20costs%20that%20get%20achieved%20through%20illegal%20payments%2C%20perceived%20stronger%20work%20ethic%2C%20customer%20preferences%20or%20the%20mindset%20that%20foreign%20workers%20are%20easier%20to%20exploit%20because%20they%20have%20limited%20knowledge%20of%20labour%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20notable%20example%20is%20the%20lawsuit%20against%20Meta%20Platforms%2C%20which%20alleges%20the%20company%20systematically%20preferred%20visa%20holders%20over%20American%20candidates%20to%20cut%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20Trump%20and%20Biden%20administrations%20have%20introduced%20measures%20to%20tighten%20regulations%20around%20the%20H-1B%20system%2C%20increasing%20scrutiny%20of%20employers%20and%20adjusting%20wage%20requirements.%20However%2C%20experts%20warn%20that%20such%20changes%20could%20have%20far-reaching%20consequences%20for%20Indian%20professionals%2C%20who%20received%2072.3%25%20of%20all%20H-1B%20visas%20issued%20between%20October%202022%20and%20September%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJidesh%20Kumar%2C%20managing%20partner%20at%20King%20Stubb%20%26amp%3B%20Kasiva%2C%20a%20corporate%20law%20firm%2C%20emphasises%20the%20US%20economy's%20reliance%20on%20H-1B%20visas%20to%20address%20skilled%20labour%20shortages%2C%20particularly%20in%20technology%2C%20engineering%2C%20and%20healthcare%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%20He%20cautions%20that%20tightening%20the%20program%20could%20drive%20global%20talent%20to%20other%20destinations%20such%20as%20Canada%20or%20the%20UK%2C%20potentially%20undermining%20the%20US's%20position%20as%20a%20leader%20in%20innovation%20and%20economic%20growth.%20%26quot%3BTech%20giants%20and%20startups%20alike%20depend%20on%20H-1B%20professionals%20for%20cutting-edge%20research%20and%20product%20development.%20Many%20also%20go%20on%20to%20become%20entrepreneurs%2C%20creating%20jobs%20and%20boosting%20the%20economy%26quot%3B%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20Immigration%20Council%20disputes%20claims%20that%20the%20H-1B%20program%20harms%20American%20workers%2C%20citing%20research%20that%20shows%20H-1B%20workers%20are%20paid%20well%20above%20national%20averages.%20In%202021%2C%20their%20median%20salary%20was%20%24108%2C000%2C%20compared%20to%20%2445%2C760%20for%20all%20US%20workers.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741262760000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2F85btsje8_h1b-visa-istock_625x300_06_March_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fh-1b-visa-why-us-has-warned-employers-to-hire-americans-over-migrant-workers-how-it-impacts-indians-7862390%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20the%20heart%20of%20this%20controversy%20lies%20the%20Equal%20Employment%20Opportunity%20Commission's%20(EEOC)%20investigation%20into%20the%20matter%2C%20aimed%20at%20safeguarding%20jobs%20for%20US%20workers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fh-1b-visa-why-us-has-warned-employers-to-hire-americans-over-migrant-workers-how-it-impacts-indians-7862390%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Thousands%20Of%20Indians%20In%20US%20Are%20Living%20In%20Fear%20Of%20%26quot%3BSelf-Deportation%26quot%3B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThousands%20of%20Indians%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20who%20migrated%20as%20minors%20under%20the%20H-4%20visa%2C%20now%20face%20an%20uncertain%20future%20as%20they%20approach%20the%20age%20of%2021.%20Under%20current%20immigration%20laws%20in%20the%20US%2C%20they%20will%20no%20longer%20qualify%20as%20dependents%20of%20their%20H1-B%20visa-holder%20parents.%20Until%20now%2C%20they%20had%20two%20years%20to%20transition%20to%20another%20visa%20status%20after%20'ageing%20out%2C'%20but%20recent%20shifts%20in%20immigration%20policy%20have%20thrown%20their%20future%20into%20doubt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20are%20now%20exploring%20other%20options%2C%20including%20immigrating%20to%20countries%20like%20Canada%20or%20the%20UK%2C%20which%20have%20more%20flexible%20policies.%20The%20massive%20backlog%20in%20the%20US%20employment-based%20green%20card%20system%20disproportionately%20affects%20Indian%20immigrants.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Citizenship%20and%20Immigration%20Services%20(USCIS)%20recently%20announced%20the%20registration%20period%20for%20H-1B%20visas%20for%20fiscal%20year%202026.%20The%20process%20opens%20on%20March%207%20and%20runs%20through%20March%2024.%20The%20H-1B%20visa%2C%20a%20non-immigrant%20visa%2C%20allows%20US%20companies%20to%20employ%20foreign%20workers%20in%20specialised%20occupations%20that%20require%20theoretical%20or%20technical%20expertise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20H-1B%20cap%20remains%2065%2C000%20visas%20per%20year%2C%20with%20an%20additional%2020%2C000%20for%20applicants%20with%20US%20master's%20degrees.%20The%20USCIS%20has%20introduced%20a%20beneficiary-centric%20selection%20process%20to%20reduce%20fraud%20and%20ensure%20fair%20selection.%20The%20new%20registration%20fee%20is%20%24215.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20Times%20of%20India%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fhyderabad%2Fover-1-lakh-dependent-indian-youth-fear-self-deportation-from-us%2Farticleshow%2F118742957.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20of%20March%202023%2C%20nearly%201.34%20lakh%20Indian%20children%20were%20expected%20to%20age%20out%20of%20dependent%20visa%20status%20before%20their%20families%20secured%20green%20cards.%20The%20backlog%20in%20the%20US%20immigration%20system%20means%20many%20will%20face%20long%20waits%20for%20permanent%20residency%2C%20with%20some%20applications%20projected%20to%20take%20anywhere%20between%2012%20to%20100%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20ruling%20from%20a%20Texas%20court%20blocking%20work%20permits%20for%20new%20applicants%20under%20the%20Deferred%20Action%20for%20Childhood%20Arrivals%20(DACA)%20program%20has%20worsened%20the%20situation.%20DACA%20provides%20temporary%2C%20renewable%20two-year%20protection%20from%20deportation%20for%20undocumented%20youth%2C%20including%20those%20who%20lose%20dependent%20status%20after%20turning%2021.%20Without%20this%20provision%2C%20many%20Indian%20youth%20now%20fear%20an%20uncertain%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20Senator%20Bernie%20Sanders%2C%20a%20leading%20progressive%2C%20had%20criticised%20the%20H-1B%20program%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20arguing%20that%20it%20primarily%20benefits%20corporations%20by%20bringing%20in%20lower-paid%20foreign%20workers%20instead%20of%20hiring%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20main%20function%20of%20the%20H-1B%20program%20is%20not%20to%20hire%20'the%20best%20and%20the%20brightest'%20but%20rather%20to%20replace%20good-paying%20American%20jobs%20with%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20lower-paid%20guest%20workers%20from%20abroad%20who%20are%20often%20treated%20as%20indentured%20servants%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Sanders%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Sanders%20has%20proposed%20an%20amendment%20to%20the%20Laken%20Riley%20Act%2C%20aiming%20to%20double%20H-1B%20visa%20fees%20to%20generate%20%24370%20million%20annually%2C%20funding%20nearly%2020%2C000%20scholarships%20for%20American%20students%20in%20STEM%20fields.%20He%20has%20also%20proposed%20to%20increase%20wages%20for%20H-1B%20workers%20to%20at%20least%20the%20median%20local%20wage%2C%20preventing%20companies%20from%20undercutting%20American%20salaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Sanders%20also%20took%20aim%20at%20billionaires%20like%20Tesla%20owner%20Elon%20Musk%20and%20Indian-American%20entrepreneur%20Vivek%20Ramaswamy%20for%20their%20support%20of%20the%20H-1B%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BElon%20Musk%2C%20the%20wealthiest%20man%20in%20the%20world%2C%20and%20other%20multi-billionaires%20claim%20the%20H-1B%20program%20is%20vital%20due%20to%20a%20shortage%20of%20highly%20skilled%20workers.%20In%20my%20view%2C%20they%20are%20dead%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECiting%20Economic%20Policy%20Institute%20data%2C%20he%20said%20that%20between%202022%20and%202023%2C%20the%20top%2030%20H-1B%20employers%20laid%20off%2085%2C000%20American%20workers%20while%20hiring%20over%2034%2C000%20guest%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741262760000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2F40iqstbo_h1b-visa-istock_625x300_05_December_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fh1b-visa-india-us-immigration-why-are-thousands-of-indians-in-us-in-fear-of-self-deportation-7861676%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Thousands%20of%20Indians%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20who%20migrated%20as%20minors%20under%20the%20H-4%20visa%2C%20now%20face%20an%20uncertain%20future%20as%20they%20approach%20the%20age%20of%2021.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%