'Amour%20Events%2C%20reached%20out%20the%20following%20month.%20They%20produced%20weddings%20in%20Beverly%20Hills%20and%20hired%20me%20as%20one%20of%20their%20on-site%20coordinators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20began%20calling%20to%20book%20events%20from%20my%20Google%20listing.%20When%20I%20started%20booking%20several%20events%20per%20day%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20needed%20to%20hire%20trustworthy%20people%20to%20lead%20them.%20I%20built%20an%20internal%20leadership%20training%20program%20to%20teach%20my%20leaders%20how%20to%20keep%20clients%20happy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20provided%20luxury%20staff%20and%20helped%20coordinate%20event%20spaces%2C%20schedules%2C%20and%20timings.%20From%20October%202019%20to%20February%202020%2C%20I%20was%20gathering%20solid%20momentum%2C%20and%20my%20revenue%20was%20growing.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fa357b45-93f3-4e67-bf90-5b9b0e7a077b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECOVID%20shut%20our%20revenue%20to%20zero%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20work%20during%202020.%20It%20was%20disheartening.%20I%20got%20a%20job%20as%20a%20mortgage%20lender%20again.%20Interest%20rates%20had%20cratered%2C%20and%20the%20lending%20business%20was%20booming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20My%20business%20was%20still%20shut%20down.%20But%20I%20got%20a%20call%20from%20a%20client%20asking%20to%20hire%2050%20people%20in%20a%20week's%20time%20for%20a%20wedding.%20They%20must%20have%20found%20my%20website%20or%20Google%20listing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20said%20yes%2C%20hoping%20I%20could%20figure%20it%20out.%20Other%20staffing%20agencies%20had%20closed%20down%20or%20were%20scared%20of%20COVID.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20contacted%20the%20managers%20at%20other%20agencies%20and%20asked%20them%20to%20help%20me.%20I%20figured%20that%20if%20I%20had%20good%20leadership%2C%20I%20could%20pad%20the%20rest%20out%20with%20less%20experienced%20staff.%20After%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCD9U00ngr6j%2F%3Fimg_index%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethat%20event%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20was%20back%20in%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20client%20ended%20up%20being%20a%20big%20wedding%20producer%20and%20loved%20our%20service.%20She%20gave%20us%20referrals%20and%20repeat%20business.%20In%202021%2C%20I%20expanded%20very%20quickly%20because%20I%20said%20yes%20to%20everyone%20and%20captured%20a%20lot%20of%20business%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20made%20about%20%24250%2C000%20in%20revenue%20in%202021%2C%20even%20though%20it%20was%20half%20a%20year%20of%20trading.%20We%20worked%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCWCkOHrBSJk%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Kid%20LAROI's%2018th%20birthday%20party%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20week%20his%20song%20with%20Justin%20Bieber%20became%20No.%201%20on%20the%20charts.%20They%20did%20a%20performance%20with%20pyrotechnics%20at%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHiring%20my%20first%20full-time%20employee%20was%20a%20huge%20factor%20in%20our%20ability%20to%20scale.%20I%20hired%20a%20young%2C%20quick-texting%20micro%20influencer.%20She%20was%20naturally%20good%20at%20finding%20people%20to%20help%20me%20last%20minute%20and%20handling%20back-and-forth%20communications.%20I%20think%20the%20scariest%20part%20for%20entrepreneurs%20is%20hiring%20the%20first%20employee%2C%20but%20it%20has%20a%20big%20impact%20on%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%20and%202023%2C%20we%20brought%20in%20around%20%24950%2C000%20in%20revenue.%20We%20focused%20on%20building%20infrastructure%20and%20internal%20systems%20and%20brought%20in%20just%20over%20%241%20million%20in%20revenue%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2216222a4c-31a8-47fa-b1f0-11155d4b93e3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20have%20to%20be%20honest%20with%20yourself%20as%20a%20CEO%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20to%20be%20a%20CEO%20and%20lead%2C%20you%20have%20to%20reinvent%20yourself%20and%20be%20willing%20to%20learn.%20You%20have%20to%20have%20uncomfortable%20conversations%20with%2