0it's%20about%20teaching%20financial%20habits%20that%20will%20serve%20them%20for%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2235bb78be-36ee-497c-b7bf-4f56b6fb8303%5C%22%3EWe%20made%20all%20our%20kids%20a%20deal%20when%20they%20got%20their%20first%20jobs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcut-kids-allowance-grateful-money-jobs-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildren%20started%20working%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20all%20around%20the%20ages%20of%2015%20or%2016%2C%20I%20made%20them%20a%20deal.%20I%20would%20provide%20logistical%20support%2C%20such%20as%20transportation%2C%20work%20clothing%20or%20uniforms%2C%20and%20the%20occasional%20Slurpee%20on%20a%20hot%20day.%20In%20return%2C%20they'd%20contribute%2025%25%20of%20their%20earned%20income%20to%20a%20Roth%20IRA%20each%20year.%20Then%20I'd%20match%20their%20contributions%203-to-1%2C%20so%20that%20essentially%2C%20100%25%20of%20their%20earned%20income%20would%20be%20put%20into%20their%20IRA%2C%20up%20to%20that%20year's%20contribution%20limit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20they%20were%20earning%20well%20under%20the%20contribution%20limit.%20As%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstrategies-earn-more-money-negotiate-raise-start-side-hustle-budgetnista-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincome%20grew%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20math%20started%20to%20shift.%20Their%20contribution%20represented%20a%20larger%20portion%20of%20the%20yearly%20limit%2C%20and%20our%20contribution%20shrunk.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20a%20year%20with%20a%20%246%2C000%20limit%2C%20if%20their%2025%25%20was%20%242%2C500%2C%20then%20Mom%20and%20Dad%20were%20only%20chipping%20in%20%243%2C500.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20plan%20had%20two%20primary%20goals.%20First%2C%20it%20created%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fhow-to-save-money%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehabit%20of%20saving%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Second%2C%20compounding%20growth%20requires%20time.%20The%20earlier%20you%20start%2C%20the%20more%20your%20money%20works%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222fa44025-2b25-43f6-bfe9-1fb5b81428a2%5C%22%3EWe%20chose%20to%20open%20Roth%20IRAs%20for%20a%20few%20reasons%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20a%20Roth%20IRA%20instead%20of%20a%20savings%20account%3F%20Investing%20in%20a%20Roth%20IRA%20at%20a%20young%20age%20provides%20a%20distinct%20tax%20advantage%20that's%20hard%20to%20replicate%20as%20you%20get%20older.%20Because%20most%20teens%20don't%20earn%20a%20lot%20of%20money%2C%20they%20typically%20don't%20have%20to%20pay%20income%20taxes%20(in%202025%2C%20people%20who%20make%20under%20%2415%2C000%20a%20year%20don't%20have%20to%20file%20a%20tax%20return).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpening%20a%20Roth%20IRA%20for%20a%20teen%20is%20easier%20than%20most%20people%20think.%20Many%20brokerage%20firms%20offer%20custodial%20Roth%20IRAs%2C%20meaning%20a%20parent%20manages%20the%20account%20until%20the%20child%20turns%2018%20or%2021%20(depending%20on%20the%20state).%20Once%20the%20account%20is%20open%2C%20they%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-to-buy-stock%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvest%20in%20something%20simple%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20an%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20Index%20fund%2C%20and%20watch%20their%20money%20grow%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20parents%20assume%20their%20kid%20needs%20to%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Breal%26quot%3B%20job%20to%20open%20a%20Roth%20IRA%2C%20but%20that's%20not%20true.%20Any%20earned%20income%20qualifies%2C%20whether%20it's%20from%20babysitting%2C%20mowing%20lawns%2C%20tutoring%2C%20or%20a%20part-time%20job.%20Just%20make%20sure%20they%20keep%20track%20of%20that%20income%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20if%20it%20meets%20the%20threshold%2C%20report%20it%20for%20tax%20purposes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20any%20of%20my%20children%20need%20the%20money%20before%20retirement%20for%20a%20major%20expense%20%E2%80%94%20like%20buying%20a%20first%20home%20or%20even%20an%20emergency%20%E2%80%94%20Roth%20IRA%20contributions%20can%20be%20withdrawn%20at%20any%20time%20without%20penalty.%20It's%20not%20just%20about%20saving%20for%20old%20age%3B%20it's%20about%20creating%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-financial-safety-net-money-independence-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancial%20safety%20net%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20life.%20That%20safety%20net%20can%20open%20up%20options%20at%20many%20different%20points%20during%20life%2C%20including%20feeling%20comfortable%20leaving%20the%20workforce%20to%20care%20for%20children%20or%20parents%2C%20being%20able%20to%20start%20a%20business%2C%20or%20just%20meeting%20the%20demands%20of%20the%20expensive%20times%20in%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20parents%2C%20we%20spend%20so%20much%20time%20worrying%20about%20our%20kids'%20future%20%E2%80%94%20college%2C%20careers%2C%20relationships.%20But%20one%20of%20the%20greatest%20gifts%20we%20can%20give%20them%20is%20a%20head%20start%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Ffinancial-independence-retire-early%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancial%20independence%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Helping%20your%20teen%20open%20a%20Roth%20IRA%20sets%20them%20up%20for%20long-term%20wealth%2C%20but%20it%20also%20teaches%20them%20valuable%20habits%20that%20will%20serve%20them%20well%20into%20adulthood.%20The%20process%20is%20straightforward%2C%20and%20the%20benefits%20are%20undeniable.%20By%20taking%20this%20small%20step%20today%2C%20you're%20giving%20your%20child%20the%20freedom%20and%20security%20to%20make%20better%20financial%20choices%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhelped-kids-contribute-maxiumum-roth-iras-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741255622000%2C