%2C%20the%20White%20House%20could%20make%20it%20more%20difficult%20to%20get%20those%20deals%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20digital%20side%2C%20advertisers%20are%20spending%20most%20of%20their%20budgets%20with%20Google%20and%20Meta%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrands-scared-of-culture-war-controversy-its-hurting-media-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20are%20avoiding%20news%20altogether%3C%2Fa%3E%20out%20of%20fear%20of%20political%20backlash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20now%2C%20most%20news%20outlets%20have%20developed%20multiple%20revenue%20streams%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-ny-times-big-plans-for-nyt-cooking-app-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubscriptions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20events%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-tests-pilot-pays-publishers-shoppers-native-commerce-advertising-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ee-commerce%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20like%20to%20offset%20their%20dependence%20on%20advertising%20and%20support%20their%20newsgathering%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20people%20won't%20pay%20for%20news%20they%20don't%20trust%20it%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22df6e945f-f802-49b8-9898-a97af30372a4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMoving%20the%20needle%20on%20trust%20is%20hard%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Freutersinstitute.politics.ox.ac.uk%2Fstrategies-building-trust-news-what-public-say-they-want-across-four-countries%23header--4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20back%20up%20the%20strategies%20newsrooms%20like%20the%20Times%20and%20Journal%20are%20employing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20is%20that%20moving%20the%20needle%20on%20trust%20is%20a%20slow%20process%20and%20each%20strategy%20doesn't%20work%20equally%20with%20all%20groups%20of%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226027%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Washington%20Post%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ac4f4f97a74af2e008b4621%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223846%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%20has%20faced%20backlash%20over%20changes%20to%20its%20opinion%20strategy.%3Cp%3EManuel%20Balce%20Ceneta%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20transparency%20moves%20only%20work%20with%20people%20who%20already%20are%20inclined%20to%20trust%20you%20and%20can%20backfire%20with%20those%20who%20don't%2C%20for%20example%2C%20said%20Nic%20Newman%2C%20a%20researcher%20at%20the%20Reuters%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20Journalism.%20Abandon%20your%20editorial%20heritage%20or%20change%20your%20newsroom%20makeup%20too%20drastically%2C%20and%20in%20trying%20to%20appeal%20to%20new%20people%2C%20you%20risk%20alienating%20your%20base.%20(The%20Washington%20Post%20lost%2075%2C000%20subscriptions%20after%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-wapo-columnists-must-defend-free-markets-personal-liberties-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echanged%20its%20opinion%20strategy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20on%20top%20of%20an%20earlier%20loss%20of%20300%2C000%20after%20it%20killed%20a%20presidential%20endorsement%20of%20Kamala%20Harris%2C%20NPR%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2025%2F02%2F28%2Fnx-s1-5312819%2Fwashington-post-bezos-subscriptions-cancellations%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20decide%20who%20you%20want%20to%20be%20trusted%20by%2C%26quot%3B%20Newman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBandwidth%20is%20another%20limiting%20factor.%20Reporters%20can%20only%20make%20so%20many%20vertical%20videos%20on%20top%20of%20everything%20else%20they're%20doing.%20The%20Times%20publishes%20200%20articles%20a%20day%2C%20but%20only%20a%20small%20fraction%20of%20them%20turn%20into%20a%20reporter%20video.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegacy%20newsrooms%20are%20also%20tradition-bound.%20The%20Times%20isn't%20going%20to%20change%20its%20social-media%20policy%20that%20bars%20reporters%20from%20sharing%20their%20personal%20political%20opinions%2C%20even%20though%20some%20in%20the%20newsroom%20think%20it's%20time%20to%20abandon%20the%20tradition%20of%20appearing%20objective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20analysts%20and%20newsroom%20insiders%20think%20mainstream%20outlets%20should%20play%20to%20their%20strengths%2C%20even%20if%20it%20means%20limiting%20their%20ambitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstitutional%20journalism%20at%20the%20moment%20is%20definitely%20being%20diminished%20and%20its%20trust%20is%20being%20affected%2C%26quot%3B%20Newman%20said.%20%26quot%3BCan%20that%20be%20reversed%3F%20It%20requires%20a%20mix%20of%20all%20these%20things.%20Not%20all%20these%20things%20are%20possible.%20It%20requires%20engaging%20in%20community%20building%2C%20which%20is%20one%20thing%20that%20influencers%20are%20really%20good%20at%20and%20traditional%20media%20is%20not.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20news%20execs%20believe%20there's%20still%20the%20opportunity%20to%20grow%20and%20reach%20new%20audiences.%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20data%20published%20in%20October%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fjournalism%2F2024%2F10%2F10%2Fwhere-americans-turn-for-election-news%2Fpj_2024-10-10_2024-election-news_2-05%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshowed%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20example%2C%20that%20younger%20Republicans%20were%20more%20likely%20than%20their%20older%20counterparts%20to%20turn%20to%20CNN%2C%20the%20Times%2C%20and%20other%20mainstream%20outlets%20for%20election%20news.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKahn%20said%20there%20are%20many%20curious%20readers%20that%20the%20Times%20hasn't%20reached%20yet.%20A%20Times%20rep%20said%20its%20top%2010%20states%20for%20subscriber%20growth%20rates%20in%20the%20last%20five%20years%20were%20all%20outside%20the%20Northeast%20and%20West%20Coast%20and%20that%20the%20South%20is%20leading%20the%20way%20in%20audience%20growth.%20The%20Midwest%20and%20South%20%E2%80%94%20which%20largely%20voted%20for%20Trump%20in%202024%20%E2%80%94%20make%20up%2042%25%20of%20its%20readership%20so%20far%20this%20year%2C%20the%20rep%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Pew%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fjournalism%2F2024%2F10%2F10%2Fwhere-americans-turn-for-election-news%2Fpj_2024-10-10_2024-election-news_2-04%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20than%20twice%20as%20many%20Democrats%20as%20Republicans%20rely%20on%20the%20Times%20for%20political%20news.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20making%20a%20claim%20that%20lots%20of%20people%20who%20are%20hard-core%20MAGA%20right%20are%20among%20the%20main%20demo%20of%20New%20York%20Times%20readers%2C%26quot%3B%20Kahn%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20more%20people%20consider%20themselves%20partisans%2C%20the%20less%20likely%20they%20are%20to%20want%20to%20engage%20with%20a%20news%20brand%20that%20isn't%20aligned%20with%20their%20partisan%20interest.%20But%20I%20do%20think%20those%20people%20get%20a%20lot%20more%20attention%20than%20they%20actually%20represent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmedia-trust-crisis-democracy-trump-threats-nyt-wsj-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741255622000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c772d069253ccddf984544%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmedia-trust-crisis-democracy-trump-threats-nyt-wsj-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20mass%20media%20faces%20its%20lowest%20trust%20levels%20in%20five%20decades%2C%20at%20the%20same%20time%20it's%20being%20targeted%20by%20Trump%20and%20his%20allies.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lmoses%40insider.com%20(Lucia%20Moses)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsi