C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eculling%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Even%20Google%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-layoffs-job-cuts-document-impacted-teams-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrimming%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2208816013-417a-4f73-93b8-1dcbdf8920a5%5C%22%3EMicrosoft's%20termination%20letter%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20who%20were%20let%20go%20in%20Microsoft's%20recent%20round%20of%20performance%20cuts%20got%20termination%20letters%20explaining%20the%20abrupt%20exit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reason(s)%20for%20the%20termination%20of%20your%20employment%20include%20your%20job%20performance%20has%20not%20met%20minimum%20performance%20standards%20and%20expectations%20for%20your%20position%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20letters%2C%20which%20BI%20viewed.%20%26quot%3BYou%20are%20relieved%20of%20all%20job%20duties%20effective%20immediately%20and%20your%20access%20to%20Microsoft%20systems%2C%20accounts%2C%20and%20buildings%20will%20be%20removed%20effective%20today.%20You%20are%20not%20to%20perform%20any%20further%20work%20on%20behalf%20of%20Microsoft.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letters%20mentioned%20severance%20but%20said%20medical%2C%20prescription%2C%20and%20dental%20benefits%20ended%20on%20the%20last%20day%20of%20employment.%20The%20letters%20also%20said%20Microsoft%20would%20consider%20past%20performance%20and%20termination%20if%20the%20person%20applied%20for%20other%20jobs%20at%20the%20company%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20Microsoft%20we%20focus%20on%20high%20performance%20talent%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20company%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20recently.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20always%20working%20on%20helping%20people%20learn%20and%20grow.%20When%20people%20are%20not%20performing%2C%20we%20take%20the%20appropriate%20action.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2253e86286-da1c-4195-bd69-176d8a0d9735%5C%22%3E'Right%20to%20fire'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDeena%20Merlen%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20Reavis%20Page%20Jump%20LLP%2C%20told%20BI%20her%20law%20firm%20had%20received%20more%20inquiries%20about%20performance-based%20layoffs%20as%20of%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEmployers%20generally%20have%20the%20right%20to%20fire%2C%20just%20as%20an%20employee%20has%20the%20right%20to%20quit%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAs%20long%20as%20Microsoft's%20alleged%20performance-based%20reasons%20are%20not%20for%20some%20other%2C%20unlawful%20reason%2C%20Microsoft%20is%20within%20its%20rights%20to%20engage%20in%20these%20layoffs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20has%20no%20obligation%20to%20provide%20severance%2C%20but%20such%20agreements%20often%20come%20with%20a%20release%20of%20legal%20claims%20that%20can%20protect%20the%20company%20from%20lawsuits%2C%20Merlen%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22debc0be8-e925-4d9e-a4b0-d314003dc1ba%5C%22%3EStack%20ranking%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%202014%2C%20Microsoft%20used%20a%20controversial%20system%20to%20evaluate%20employee%20performance.%20Called%20stack%20ranking%2C%20it%20forced%20managers%20to%20put%20employees%20on%20a%20curve%20and%20cut%20the%20lowest%20performers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Microsoft%2C%20that%20meant%20managers%20had%20to%20rank%20employees%20from%201%20to%205%2C%20and%20someone%20always%20had%20to%20get%20a%205%2C%20the%20lowest%20score%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20well%20they%20or%20the%20team%20performed.%20Shaw%2C%20the%20Microsoft%20spokesperson%2C%20said%20that%20the%20system%20was%20especially%20problematic%20for%20small%20teams%20and%20that%20while%20terminating%20the%20lowest%20rung%20was%20not%20a%20companywide%20policy%2C%20it%20happened%20on%20some%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22801%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kathleen%20Hogan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a9ede665cc41019008b45d0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKathleen%20Hogan%2C%20the%20chief%20people%20officer%20at%20Microsoft.%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStack%20ranking%20was%20unpopular%20internally%20and%20was%20seen%20as%20prioritizing%20individual%20work%2C%20pitting%20employees%20against%20one%20another%20and%20creating%20a%20barrier%20to%20collaboration.%20Developers%20and%20even%20entire%20organizations%20had%20a%20tendency%20to%20reject%20acceptable%20solutions%20to%20problems%20if%20they%20hadn't%20developed%20those%20solutions%20themselves%2C%20the%20company's%20chief%20people%20officer%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ceo-satya-nadella-company-culture-change-growth-mindset%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKathleen%20Hogan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20previously%20told%20BI.%20There's%20even%20a%20famous%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-satya-nadella-company-culture-2017-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecartoon%20depicting%20Microsoft's%20org%20chart%20as%20warring%20factions%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221dbf3f72-d1eb-4818-ba4e-f57bcbde658b%5C%22%3E'Model%2C%20coach%2C%20care'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20officially%20abandoned%20stack%20ranking%20just%20before%20Nadella%20took%20over%20as%20CEO%20in%20early%202014.%20He%20redesigned%20the%20company's%20performance-review%20system%20around%20the%20%26quot%3Bgrowth%20mindset%26quot%3B%20concept.%20The%20idea%20is%20that%20skills%20are%20developed%20through%20hard%20work%20and%20that%20challenges%20and%20failures%20are%20opportunities%20to%20learn.%20This%20is%20counter%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bfixed%20mindset%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20assumes%20talent%20is%20innate%20and%20struggles%20are%20a%20sign%20of%20failure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENadella%20and%20his%20new%20leadership%20team%20applied%20this%20growth%20mindset%20to%20a%20new%20framework%20called%20%26quot%3Bmodel%2C%20coach%2C%20care%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20called%20on%20managers%20to%20set%20a%20positive%20example%20for%20employees%2C%20help%20staffers%20adapt%20and%20learn%2C%20and%20invest%20in%20people's%20professional%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20ranking%20employees%20from%201%20to%205%2C%20Microsoft%20moved%20to%20a%20performance-review%20system%20that%20gives%20managers%20a%20simple%20payroll%20budget%20they%20could%20divide%20and%20dole%20out%20to%20employees%20based%20on%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKevin%20Oakes%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20Institute%20for%20Corporate%20Productivity%2C%20has%20worked%20with%20Microsoft%20on%20implementing%20a%20growth%20mindset.%20He%20told%20BI%20this%20approach%20was%20a%20way%20to%20encourage%20top%20performers%20but%20noted%20that%20even%20companies%20like%20Microsoft%20need%20to%20cull%20their%20workforces%20to%20become%20leaner%20and%20higher%20performing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20high-performing%20organization%20should%20make%20sure%20employees%20are%20performing%20at%20an%20acceptable%20level%2C%20and%20they%20should%20be%20weeding%20out%20people%20who%20are%20not%20performing%20at%20an%20acceptable%20level%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BOver%20time%2C%20you%20tend%20to%20get%20a%20little%20bloated%20as%20a%20big%20company%20where%20you've%20let%20hiring%20go%20unchecked%20in%20some%20areas%20and%20need%20to%20get%20back%20to%20a%20lean%2C%20efficient%20machine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2283cfdbc8-e03f-4b5c-a0fe-b88e77399576%5C%22%3EThe%20ManageRewards%20slider%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224526%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amy%20Hood%20Microsoft%20CFO%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679b83eeeb4be2fff9a2e5ed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223140%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMicrosoft%20CFO%20Amy%20Hood.%3Cp%3EStephen%20Brashear%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20employees%20are%20evaluated%20on%20a%20scale%20from%200%20to%20200%20called%20the%20%26quot%3BManageRewards%20slider.%26quot%3B%20The%20process%20begins%20with%20frontline%20managers%2C%20who%20evaluate%20an%20employee's%20impact%20and%20recommend%20where%20they%20think%20they%20should%20land%20on%20the%20slider.%20Then%2C%20a%20higher-level%20manager%20considers%20%26quot%3Bdifferentiation%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20i.e.%2C%20making%20sure%20the%20team%20is%20distributed%20along%20the%20slider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20middle%20of%20the%20range%20is%20100%2C%20while%200%2C%2060%2C%20and%2080%20are%20lower%20performers%20and%20120%2C%20140%2C%20and%20200%20are%20higher%20performers.%20Those%20ratings%20influence%20how%20much%20an%20employee%20receives%20in%20stock%20awards%20and%20cash%20bonuses.%20A%20score%20of%20%26quot%3BImpact%2060%2C%26quot%3B%20for%20example%2C%20generally%20gives%20employees%200%25%20of%20their%20stock%20award%20and%2030%25%20of%20their%20maximum%20cash%20bonuses%20while%20the%20slightly%20higher%20rating%20of%20%26quot%3BImpact%2080%26quot%3B%20gives%20them%2060%25%20of%20their%20normal%20stock%20award%20and%2080%25%20of%20their%20maximum%20bonus.%20Shaw%2C%20Microsoft's%20spokesperson%2C%20said%20100%20would%20be%20considered%20a%20good%20score%20and%20mean%20an%20employee%20had%20met%20all%20of%20their%20objectives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20the%20company's%20senior%20leadership%20team%20gives%20managers%20a%20budget%20that%20allows%20for%20every%20employee%20on%20the%20team%20an%20average%20score%20of%20109.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20you%20want%20to%20pay%20someone%20impact%20140%20for%20doing%20an%20outstanding%20job%3F%20Find%203%20people%20you're%20giving%20Impact%20100%20so%20it's%20affordable%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20executive-level%20manager%20explained.%20%26quot%3BKeep%20this%20guy%20around.%20He'll%20be%20paying%20for%20everyone's%20bonuses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20manager%20said%20they%20typically%20had%20paid%20top%20performers%20by%20finding%20a%20set%20of%20people%20who%20failed%20in%20the%20previous%20year%20and%20giving%20them%20all%20zero%20or%20reduced%20rewards.%20This%20person%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20identified%20discussing%20sensitive%20topics.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20bad%20manager%2C%26quot%3B%20Shaw%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20certainly%20can't%20give%20everybody%20high%20rewards%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20you%20can%20give%20one%20person%20high%20rewards%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20people%20around%20100.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2248d62bfd-baaa-48f3-9025-771b7a744f94%5C%22%3EHow%20Microsoft%20handles%20low%20performers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20low%20rewards%20can%20indicate%20a%20performance%20issue%2C%20Microsoft's%20actual%20system%20for%20managing%20out%20low%20performers%20is%20separate%20from%20this%20employee-rating%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenerally%2C%20managers%20email%20an%20internal%20system%20called%20AskHR%40%20and%20request%20a%20consultation%20for%20performance%20concerns%2C%20and%20the%20manager%20will%20be%20matched%20with%20an%20internal%20consultant.%20More%20seasoned%20consultants%20are%20used%20for%20higher-level%20employees%2C%20or%20if%20the%20situation%20is%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20consultants%20give%20written%20formal%20feedback%20to%20employees%2C%20saying%20they%20delivered%20%26quot%3BLess%20Impact%20than%20Expected%26quot%3B%20and%20start%20a%20three-month%20performance-management%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20managers%20can%20cut%20low%20performers%20who%20don't%20improve%20within%20about%20four%20months%20through%20this%20process.%20But%20sometimes%20Microsoft's%20HR%20department%20concludes%20that%20managers%20haven't%20done%20enough%20performance%20coaching%2C%20one%20manager%20said%2C%20meaning%20they%20have%20not%20generated%20enough%20documentation%20showing%20employees%20have%20been%20given%20the%20opportunity%20to%20improve%20and%20have%20repeatedly%20failed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20take%20two%20or%20three%20more%2090-day%20programs%20before%20these%20employees%20are%20ousted.%20One%20high-level%20manager%20said%20the%20average%20time%20to%20exit%20a%20low%20performer%20was%20seven%20months%20from%20the%20time%20a%20manager%20notified%20HR%20about%20the%20situation%2C%20which%20often%20comes%20after%20sustained%20low%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20takes%20too%20long%20to%20performance-manage%20folks%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20executive%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20exits%20can%20be%20further%20delayed%20by%20leaves%20of%20absence.%20One%20of%20the%20Microsoft%20managers%20who%20talked%20to%20BI%20said%20employees%20sometimes%20shared%20tips%20on%20how%20to%20complicate%20the%20company's%20performance-improvement%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20common%20suggestion%3A%20If%20your%20manager%20is%20working%20to%20fire%20you%2C%20go%20to%20a%20doctor%20and%20say%20you%20have%20certain%20symptoms%2C%20get%20a%20supporting%20letter%2C%20and%20secure%20health-related%20time%20off%20work.%20This%20can%20pause%20or%20reset%20aspects%20of%20the%20process%2C%20this%20person%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShort-term%20paid%20disability%20typically%20covers%2060%20to%2090%20days%20away%20from%20work%2C%20and%20Microsoft's%20HR%20department%20can%20be%20reluctant%20to%20exit%20these%20employees%20for%20some%20time%20after%20that%2C%20the%20person%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20employees%20gaming%20the%20short-term%20disability%20policies%2C%20you%20can%20be%20talking%2012%20to%2018%20months%20to%20get%20to%20a%20point%20where%20HR%20is%20comfortable%20firing%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223414cd39-d838-4928-a7e9-318ec74a5264%5C%22%3E'One%20Year%2C%20One%20Reward'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20a%20common%20refrain%20for%20the%200-to-200%20performance%20reviews%20was%2C%20%26quot%3BOne%20Year%2C%20One%20Reward%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20employees%20are%20judged%20on%20a%20single%20year's%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20separation%20between%20rewards%20and%20the%20formal%20performance-management%20process%20gave%20flexibility%20to%20managers%20to%20%26quot%3Bharvest%20the%20budget%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20one%20manager%20said%2C%20in%20other%20words%20give%20lower%20ratings%20to%20relatively%20adequate%20performers%20so%20big%20rewards%20could%20be%20doled%20out%20to%20high%20performers.%20They%20could%20do%20this%20without%20much%20risk%20to%20the%20employment%20status%20of%20the%20adequate%20performers.%20Shaw%2C%20the%20Microsoft%20spokesperson%2C%20said%20this%20was%20not%20company%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHogan%2C%20Microsoft's%20chief%20people%20officer%2C%20in%20an%20internal%20email%20in%202023%20instructed%20managers%20to%20give%20fewer%20employees%20%26quot%3Bexceptional%20rewards%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20a%20high%20performance%20rating%20that%20leads%20to%20higher%20pay%20and%20bonuses.%20%26quot%3BMore%20will%20need%20to%20be%20at%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20range%2C%26quot%3B%20Hogan%20said%20in%20the%20email.%20Shaw%2C%20the%20spokesperson%2C%20said%20the%20email%20was%20specific%20to%20that%20year%20and%20that%20rewards%20changed%20annually%20based%20on%20factors%20like%20the%20economy%20and%20company%20performance.%20Changes%20to%20this%20year's%20rewards%20cycle%20won't%20be%20solidified%20until%20later%20in%20the%20year%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMicrosoft%20just%20summarily%20terminated%20hundreds%20of%20employees%20who%20had%20year-over-year%20insufficient%20performance%20based%20on%20rewards%2C%20without%20a%20lengthy%20documentation%20and%20feedback%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20executive%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20this%20coming%20rewards%20season%20would%20be%20more%20difficult%20on%20managers%2C%20who%20would%20have%20to%20be%20more%20careful%20about%20doling%20out%20low%20rewards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShaw%2C%20the%20Microsoft%20spokesperson%2C%20confirmed%20that%20the%20decisions%20about%20whom%20to%20cut%20came%20from%20looking%20at%20rewards%20year%20over%20year%20but%20said%20the%20company%20still%20believed%20in%20%26quot%3Bone%20year%2C%20one%20reward.%26quot%3B%20Just%20because%20an%20employee%20gets%20high%20rewards%20one%20year%2C%20for%20example%2C%20doesn't%20mean%20they've%20earned%20it%20the%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d645d521-b9bb-4b03-ac0f-6f7981671e24%5C%22%3ENew%20leaders%2C%20new%20perspectives%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Microsoft%20evaluates%20its%20performance-review%20process%2C%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20plans%20say%20the%20company%20is%20looking%20for%20perspectives%20from%20new%20leaders%20such%20as%20Suleyman%2C%20the%20former%20Google%20executive%20who%20is%20now%20Microsoft's%20CEO%20of%20AI%2C%20and%20Parikh%2C%20the%20former%20head%20of%20engineering%20at%20Meta%20who%20runs%20AI%20platforms%20at%20Microsoft.%20Shaw%20said%20that%20Suleyman%20and%20Parikh%20were%20just%20some%20of%20the%20people%20providing%20perspective%20and%20that%20Roslansky%2C%20the%20LinkedIn%20CEO%2C%20had%20also%20provided%20a%20lot%20of%20input.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20company%20will%20have%20a%20much%20stronger%20point%20of%20view%2C%20like%20some%20of%20our%20competitors%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20Microsoft%20executive%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2205e29233-7d67-4cab-99ec-08173cff2b3c%5C%22%3E'Good%20attrition'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20is%20making%20other%20changes%20to%20prioritize%20engineering%20talent%20and%20level%20out%20organizations%2C%20taking%20a%20page%20from%20Amazon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeparate%20from%20its%20performance-management%20processes%2C%20Microsoft%20is%20starting%20to%20weigh%20how%20it%20can%20become%20leaner%20and%20more%20engineering-focused.%20The%20company%20measures%20what%20it%20calls%20%26quot%3Bgood%20attrition%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20reviewed%20at%20the%20executive%20level%2C%20the%20Microsoft%20executive%20said.%20That's%20reminiscent%20of%20Amazon's%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-annual-performance-review-process-bonus-salary-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunregretted%20attrition%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%20there%20are%20no%20targets%20for%20this%20Microsoft%20metric.%20But%20the%20company%20is%20borrowing%20from%20Amazon%20in%20trying%20to%20increase%20the%20ratio%20of%20engineers%20working%20on%20projects.%20Amazon%20has%20something%20called%20the%20%26quot%3BBuilder%20Ratio%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20analyzes%20the%20ratio%20of%20software%20engineers%20to%20%26quot%3Bnon-builders%2C%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20program%20managers%20and%20project%20managers.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20try%20to%20keep%20organizations%20lean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECharlie%20Bell%2C%20Microsoft's%20security%20boss%20who%20came%20from%20Amazon's%20cloud%20unit%2C%20has%20brought%20this%20metric%20to%20Microsoft.%20Microsoft%20tracks%20the%20%26quot%3BPM%20ratio%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20the%20ratio%20of%20product%20managers%20or%20program%20managers%20to%20engineers%2C%20and%20has%20increased%20targets%20in%20the%20current%20fiscal%20year.%20For%20example%2C%20Bell's%20security%20organization%20right%20now%20is%20around%205.5%20engineers%20to%20one%20PM%2C%20and%20his%20goal%20is%20to%20reach%2010%3A1%2C%20according%20to%20a%20person%20familiar%20with%20Bell's%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aastewart%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eastewart%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20%2B1-425-344-8242.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere's%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22htt